meta.description: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club at Hartsfield–Jackson Atlanta International Airport (ATL), Concourse F. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club

location.terminalDirections: Go up to the Mezzanine Floor near Gate F10. Follow sign to the lounge.

lounge.description: The Delta Sky Club is an award-winning retreat that allows relaxation, productivity, or both.

reviews.content: Spacious and outdoor seating. Prepackaged food during COVID. Nice ambience.
Not the best lounge out there but the service is top notch. Food at the buffet is a little sad. I think there is something about the staff here that makes it my go to lounges in the ATL airport.
Very busy, yet adequate seating. I was here at 5pm and the buffet had several different hot items that were constantly being refilled.
Customer service at this lounge is great, the WiFi at this lounge is next to unusable. I could barely log into webpages from my PC so executing schoolwork or business work was a challenge.
They try but not my favorite. Food options are dated and the best feature, the sun deck, is always crowded. If you need to shower use the other Sky Club that offers them (those are cleaner).
Sky deck is great when Atlanta isn’t a sauna, food selections best of Atlanta Sky Clubs, Internet sucks the least of Atlanta Sky Clubs.
I have been to other airline clubs and I am not impressed with this one. Cardboard dish ware and plastic utensils? Breakfast very limited. This is a pet peeve but no cream for coffee? Disappointed!!
For breakfast on Thanksgiving at 9am they served brownies, stale bread rolls, cereal and dried apricots. This is first class. 👍🏽👍🏽
Nice place...high society and high class...I'm Amex Platinum and it's free for that....a place to call home when on the fly.
Very reasonable Delta lounge in the International Terminal.  Food slightly less appealing than the Sky Club in Terminal B.  Hard to pinpoint but an upgrade might be a good idea.
Most drinks are free, can upgrade at cost.  Food is very good. Only lounge I've been to with outside area overlooking runway to sit. Worth trip out to international terminal.  Very spacious.
Located in the shopping area on the mezzanine, it's a spacious lounge w/ awesome views and great food/booze/snacks. Plenty of comfy chairs and outlets and TVs. One of the nicer lounges I've been in.
Solid. Not outstanding but definitely one of the better basic lounges.
Probably the best Sky Club I've been to. It still doesn't rank with non-domestic airline clubs but it is darn good. The Sky Deck is an especially nice touch. And the staff was especially friendly.
One of the nicest Sky Clubs I've visited. Very spacious with multiple areas and a second floor. Good food options with some free hot options. Various snacks available.

Paper plates and Mac & cheese...pretty predictable. Showers are a plus, service is better at their solid JFK lounge. If you're here on domestic don't bother coming over to F; the lounge in A is solid.
Decent food selection and complimentary wine, beer, and cocktails in this lounge. Showers and bathrooms are clean and nice.
The agents here literally do not consider the Bahamas to be an international destination.
Great lounge with a nice hot food selection available in late afternoon and evening. The outdoor Sky Deck is a great place to spend some time and enjoy the nice weather.
Similar to the JFK T4 Sky Club. Large, airy, plenty of different seating areas and a cool open deck. Typical Sky Club food/drink offerings, for better or worse.
Best Sky Club at ATL. Worth going out of your way to visit if you have time. The Sky Deck is great.
Cannot see anything that makes this lounge not 4 stars. Skydeck was amazing but cold. Took advantage of the showers after a red eye-- wonderful. Nice little breakfast with vegan options.
Great amenities (sky deck) but usually packed. If you have a long layover, it's worth the journey over to the international terminal.
Nice Sky Club. Fare is the updated Sky Club food and beverage which is a step above AA and UA lounges. The Sky Deck at this lounge is great, showers are nice but water pressure is pretty low.
Great lounge but the bartender Clifton sucks. He doesn't smile and has an attitude.
Good place to relax and it utilizes lots of natural light.
Showers are clean and spacious. Water pressure very low, but otherwise nice. Outdoor lounge area with tarmac view was delightful in the morning. Everything else typical of newer Delta Sky Clubs.
Best Sky Lounge in ATL, you don't need to be flying international to gain access. Great showers, recliners and a great patio deck facing the airfield.
Best Sky Club in ATL. Cool outdoor terrace, a lounge chair area that goes beyond the normal chairs, and slightly better food options than others in terms of dessert. Wish there was more real food.
One of the best Delta lounges in the world, right up there with Narita.
The SkyDeck is very cool. Fun place to watch planes.
Spacious. Was here in early AM, looks as though it gets crowded later in day.  Decent breakfast spread of the ordinaries.  No pancake machine :(. Staff was a bit cold and bathroom small but clean.
It's okay. The seats are old and uncomfortable, but it does have showers, an outdoor terrace, and a good amount of natural light. The bar area is also nice and open.
Great retro feel. Great food. Relaxing. Felt special. Staff not overly friendly but it's a hard job and they are probably underpaid as are most of the underclass in the states.
Food and drinks are typical for domestic SkyClubs.  The large areas are nice and, of course, the patio.  Plan a sunset visit if you can.
This lounge, complete with SkyDeck(!), has many private, comfortable seating options and nooks. Plenty of plugs, cheerful staff, and roomy (two floors). The food selection is limited though.
The Shandong Airlines Flagship Lounge. This large lounge provides great service.
Brand new, hands down best Sky Club at ATL. Be sure to enjoy the outdoor SkyDeck when the weather is nice!
What a wonderful outdoor terrace-be sure to check them out in warm months. The showers are great as well.
The eight showers are worth the trip to this lounge. In addition, the lounge has a very large, outdoor patio area.
Though the drink and food choices are mediocre, the other amenities (showers in the back, outdoor SkyDeck, etc.) make this lounge quite good.
This would be the perfect lounge if food was served.
